  ShadowDensity: 1.000000
  Text: |-
    Custom Location
    
    This project enables you to recognize small to mid-sized environments in two simple steps.
    
    Step 1: Scan the Location
    
    Open the Custom Location Lens in Lens Explorer.
    Scan up to five areas within the location you want to recognize.
    
    Once the scanning process is complete, you will receive a location code.
    
    Step 2: Load the Location
    
    Enter the generated code into the LocationRoot field.
    Click “Load Group” to reload and activate the saved location.
    
    Step 3: Anchor your scene objects
    
    Just lilke the placeholder example you see here, place your scene object under the chidren of the location root. They will show up when you are physically exploring that location. 
    
    Best Practices
    
    This Lens works best in small to mid-sized environments.
    
    Spaces with strong visual contrast and distinct, recognizable objects produce better results.
    
    For example, a small lobby area with a couch and table is ideal.
    
    Learn more:
    https://developers.snap.com/spectacles/about-spectacles-features/apis/custom-locations
